		<p> So we are stuck in the sand all night. 
			We only slept for a few hours because we painted the various "Worse Case" scenarios in the head. 
			As it should turn out in the morning, all our worries were unfounded. </p>
		<p> Shortly after sunrise, I noticed that the first campers started the day. 
			So we got up and went in search of support.
			We asked a nicer older gentleman for help.
			Of course, he answered Aussie typically with "don'try mate" and was immediately on hand to help us.
			After only 10 minutes of shoveling and "Nice and Steady" back and forth, back and forth in front of and back, we were again on a fixed surface with all four wheels.
			We then spontaneously decided to drive the complete festival in reverse gear without turning.
			Since we were already here, we decided to put the car on the side of the path on a firm surface and go to the beach for a few more minutes, enjoy the early morning. </p>
		<p> Then we drove back to Rainbow Beach and spent the rest of the day at the campsite there with lazy ones and catch up. </p>
